cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE

Reasoning: The paper presents a morphological analyzer and generator for Russian and Ukrainian languages, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of large efficiently encoded lexicons and linguistically motivated rules, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the quality of the morphological analysis and generation, which could be relevant to information retrieval (IR) and natural language generation (NLG), making cs.IR and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible sub-categories.
